## Architecture

See [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) for detailed overview.
{% if use_ai %}
**Data backends:**

| Layer | Backend | Use case |
|-------|---------|----------|
{%- if database_backend in ('postgresql', 'azure_postgresql') %}
| Application DB | PostgreSQL | Primary relational storage |
{%- elif database_backend == 'sqlite' %}
| Application DB | SQLite | File-based relational storage (via `aiosqlite`) |
{%- endif %}
{%- if use_pgvector %}
| Vector store | pgvector | Embedding similarity search |
{%- endif %}
{%- if use_faiss %}
| Vector store | FAISS | In-process similarity search |
{%- endif %}
{%- if use_ai_search %}
| Vector store | Azure AI Search | Cloud-hosted vector + keyword search |
{%- endif %}
{%- if use_knowledge_graph %}
| Knowledge graph | {{ knowledge_graph_backend | default('networkx') }} | Entity-relation storage (`networkx`, `neo4j`, `rdflib`) |
{%- endif %}
{%- if use_agents %}
| Checkpointer | Memory / SQLite / PostgreSQL | Durable workflow state |
{%- endif %}
{%- if use_redis %}
| Cache / broker | Redis | Caching and task queue |
{%- endif %}
{% endif %}
This project follows **clean / hexagonal (ports-and-adapters) architecture**:

```
backend/src/{{ project_slug }}/
├── core/            # Pure domain — ZERO external imports
├── application/     # Use cases, services, DTOs, mappers
├── ports/           # Inbound adapters (API routes, CLI, web)
│   ├── api/middleware/  # HTTP cross-cutting concerns
{%- if api_style in ('graphql', 'both') %}
│   └── graphql/     # Strawberry GraphQL schema, resolvers, types
{%- endif %}
├── adapters/        # Outbound adapters (DB, cache, messaging)
├── infrastructure/  # Low-level (database, HTTP, security, profiling, observability)
├── config/          # Settings, DI container
{%- if use_ai %}
├── ai/              # LLM/agent tooling
{%- endif %}
└── utils/           # Shared utilities
```

